        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d551030e-9519-43e1-af06-36f39d454699",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1. Purpose"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b19b1f34-5162-4942-b5ee-ec1b246680d7",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to define the procedure for reporting to regulatory authorities in compliance with ISO13485. This SOP ensures that all necessary regulatory notifications and submissions are completed accurately, in a timely manner, and in accordance with applicable regulatory requirements."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "88348330-7b4b-46ab-88ae-0e4a6e2c7ebc",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "e94827e0-87ed-4f0c-9590-e1f8270d0675",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2. Scope"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d1287e6f-b851-4d55-b385-c0134f777572",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This SOP applies to all regulatory reporting activities required by relevant authorities, including incident reporting, change notifications, adverse event reporting, product recalls, and post-market surveillance activities. It applies to all employees involved in generating, reviewing, or approving regulatory reports."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "95ef7bdb-aeb9-4532-90b6-6129b9eec22b",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "8bc7a3dc-de5f-48fa-8ce0-55d11922f68b",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3. Responsibilities"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "de824346-bdb9-40a7-a5f6-55b86de33a50",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "df892ce3-66d3-4651-9474-620935f10393",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3.1. Regulatory Affairs"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c18ba7c3-2e48-43f0-9746-5496002169d7",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Responsible for identifying reporting requirements, preparing and submitting reports, and ensuring compliance with applicable regulatory requirements."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "5439dc6b-e974-4e94-9cad-d8ac8af21fe4",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "4bf6d21a-3731-4ff8-9864-0ba5f1a75fd6",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3.2. Quality Assurance (QA)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1ecb4eab-afc1-4546-bc72-e4fa81f14839",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Supports data collection and documentation for reporting, and assists Regulatory Affairs in tracking post-market surveillance activities."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7a1fcc11-2448-42ad-8040-48ff2d42316d",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d8b9908e-e91d-47d6-910b-1f4132bfac6e",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3.3. Department Heads"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "fd57db36-5e35-4f2e-9aac-fddce84e7b26",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Ensure prompt communication of reportable events or changes within their departments to Regulatory Affairs."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "6f7799c2-c2ed-48f5-86f0-ff90b6edcb8b",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "5dc2ca1c-6172-47d8-a31d-8a4f179dab30",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3.4. Management"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "12235049-0c55-4d00-88f4-e570f97c9563",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Provides final approval for regulatory reports when necessary and ensures adequate resources are allocated for compliance."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "11e6aeab-5a54-4899-89f9-506a563576e0",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b1368d51-c413-451d-af74-5b1fbc553b5a",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "4. Definitions"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "67f31224-5486-4919-90e9-3f54975bc8e9",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7a2d14ee-5f5b-4228-bee9-aa3d323b87fb",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "4.1. Regulatory Reporting"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "2a117a88-2fc4-44f8-ba16-e34c829f5f9d",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The process of notifying relevant authorities about reportable events, product changes, adverse events, or other information required by law or regulations."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "bd474536-83ee-47b9-b383-4c94e377368f",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7fa9e52b-068e-4bdc-9967-63c7e9fde112",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "4.2. Adverse Event"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "e17cb27c-5a70-4304-8698-2da35a41277d",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Any undesirable experience associated with the use of a product that may pose a risk to health or safety."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ccedd584-e068-4d30-b7bd-ba3beed0500d",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b0a56d44-c1c1-4928-94ef-daef1dfa615a",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "4.3. Post-Market Surveillance"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "93364853-53ee-4437-9e0e-a0314c140423",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Ongoing activities to monitor the safety and effectiveness of a product after it has been released to the market."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "8019d43c-4fbb-4b42-a06d-be691c03265d",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ee5253c0-6245-4301-ab44-79588d98cd0b",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "5. General Reporting Guidelines"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1399da0a-7858-467f-a39a-e1faa2ea73be",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "dd12d1ac-9589-4cb8-92f9-8730202d8a31",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "5.1. Timeliness"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "5545fda6-336c-41cf-b32b-45ad79e11c6a",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Ensure all reports are submitted within the timeframes specified by applicable regulatory authorities."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "68486aa6-6e9e-48ac-8a59-43a88af888b9",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "88bdd496-324a-4f1d-aa9f-7cb3e3d40110",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "5.2. Accuracy"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "fa196bec-0708-4c00-ab7d-cf536d5d83f5",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Ensure all information in reports is accurate, complete, and supported by relevant data."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c1bdd922-f1b7-4fdb-9622-94e9a4ab1d18",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "08035d2c-0467-4186-b285-183ebe8edcbd",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "5.3. Documentation"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f36943f1-a769-48fd-8a8e-63f9578a3a88",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Retain records of all submitted reports and any related correspondence with regulatory authorities."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f3b48140-1617-470e-acb8-4b8291e10597",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "0665a963-774d-41ad-8dfb-8386befb7043",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6. Regulatory Reporting Process"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1dc0c4de-fcda-48ed-a2c8-c4730cc69b94",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "e1f3e0b1-50da-436e-8619-fed3b4598e22",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6.1. Identification of Reporting Requirement"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d287c6f8-88f9-480e-b763-f1517f0c372c",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Regulatory Affairs, in collaboration with QA, monitors regulatory requirements and identifies events or changes that must be reported."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "89cc7d16-2455-4224-b5a2-7fbb0a171aaa",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Sources of Reporting Triggers:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "2ea65aea-e051-4201-a3de-4f125042f634",
      "type": "li",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "566562e1-3eca-4b88-8ebb-d705ccb4cbd8",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "This includes adverse events, recalls, field safety notices, significant product changes, or findings from post-market surveillance activities."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7666a521-8b61-454e-b696-6d0aab89ca95",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "9bc6df74-9c4f-462f-abe3-20a2b9488646",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6.2. Data Collection and Documentation"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ad370279-b3a9-4937-bfb1-6765a9af122e",
      "type": "li",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "4e5ead51-1e90-40ec-9e1c-c33cdb709819",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "QA, in coordination with relevant departments, gathers necessary data, including incident details, investigation findings, corrective actions, and supporting documentation."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ef03ed84-0a3b-498b-a4e9-42278e9ee2ad",
      "type": "li",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "5db083eb-cf57-4068-9059-18d1d107faaf",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Ensure all documentation meets regulatory standards and is stored securely for future reference and audits."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "4680d42e-7fb9-4be8-a7a0-a23598c0d6a7",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "fd441859-6d25-421e-8cb0-705d5ea34ce8",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6.3. Preparation of Regulatory Report"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d5af2c60-4ea4-45ef-9553-182f6596c551",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Regulatory Affairs prepares the regulatory report according to the specific format and requirements of the relevant authority."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "3eb314e5-daf4-48bc-9f08-64efe870b970",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Content Requirements:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "5f8eb866-dddd-4405-9dff-6d0c0d652816",
      "type": "li",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "fc3edc3e-8f80-4243-9f2a-198449268d1a",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Include product details, description of the event or change, assessment of risks, corrective actions taken, and any other data required by the regulatory authority."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "277eb6c1-171d-4c55-854c-3a5c6da861e6",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "fcf2d3a7-7db5-4ba3-88de-1bc98de93f13",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6.4. Internal Review and Approval"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1a7bbd1c-107e-4c9c-977b-33a1dc7ee6a7",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The completed report is reviewed by QA and relevant Department Heads to ensure accuracy and compliance."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "823bf560-7696-4ef2-b832-16734f6264de",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Management Approval"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "52e73802-d340-41c3-8b39-de8ed82e9482",
      "type": "li",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "b604fce3-2549-4604-a198-449fa4f61e92",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "High-impact reports, such as those involving recalls or serious adverse events, require management approval prior to submission."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b842d4b6-9a92-41b1-b274-d82e20082748",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c38eb8db-6996-4193-8dc6-94840c0784fb",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6.5. Submission to Regulatory Authority"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "3d54bef2-a18a-49f7-adbe-c4994b4d98e9",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Regulatory Affairs submits the report to the relevant regulatory authority within the required timeframe and using the specified method (e.g., electronic submission portal, email)."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "6a0716ed-1dc6-4a4b-8140-58f18fc89928",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "bold": true,
          "text": "Submission Confirmation"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ed85a68f-5a4e-454f-a1c5-6e15809e123b",
      "type": "li",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "e6266d6c-3af0-4881-824a-21aee852f595",
          "type": "lic",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Obtain confirmation of receipt from the authority, where applicable, and record the submission date and confirmation details."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "09696db2-3ff7-4598-baa7-0991b4db718e",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "0a654ec7-de9c-462f-b607-814412c90383",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "6.6. Follow-Up and Additional Reporting"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c486d317-89d4-4a6e-b775-4cdf5219f533",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "If additional information or follow-up reports are requested by the regulatory authority, Regulatory Affairs coordinates with QA and other departments to provide timely responses."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "99da660e-ad9b-4641-98c4-7453ef5f932e",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Document any follow-up submissions and maintain communication records with the regulatory authority."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "02cf33a3-7809-48a4-93b2-721e476dab69",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1ad816c4-e0fc-4e1b-a7cc-51afe43e91d3",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "7. Post-Submission Documentation and Record Keeping"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b370c192-9b34-4e79-a3be-f087d7b4e8ce",
      "type": "h2",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "71799906-dd67-4494-8262-b43bfae8ae03",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "7.1. Retention of Records"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "027408d7-d784-4f55-a87e-6ac76d63ab7d",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Keep copies of all regulatory reports, supporting documentation, and correspondence for the retention period specified by regulatory requirements."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "7ace5eff-3987-43e7-a191-25cadd013b1c",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a6934d15-6a66-4cc7-900e-b9fb2f704960",
      "type": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "7.2. Accessibility"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c688b814-2180-455d-98b9-2282647ad5d9",
      "type": "p",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Ensure records are accessible for audits and regulatory inspections."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "93f1187f-33cb-48f4-a297-49d864622e33",
      "type": "p",
